<paragraph id="IFRS17_54" base="F55666356"><paranum>54</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="54"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS17_P0212">The criterion in <xref id="IFRS17_X0269" base="F59119775" href="IFRS17_g53-59.dita#IFRS17_g53-59/IFRS17_g53-59_TI">paragraph 53(a)</xref> is not met if at the inception of the group an entity expects significant variability in the <xref base="F55666938" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0525">fulfilment cash flows<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0143"/></ph></xref> that would affect the measurement of the <xref base="F55667010" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0551">liability for remaining coverage<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0228"/></ph></xref> during the period before a claim is incurred. Variability in the fulfilment cash flows increases with, for example: </p><ol id="IFRS17_L0039" base="F55666358" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0213" base="F55666359">the extent of future cash flows relating to any derivatives embedded in the contracts; and</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IFRS17_P0214" base="F55666361">the length of the <xref base="F55666921" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0520">coverage period<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0060"/></ph></xref> of the <xref base="F55666942" href="IFRS17_APPA.dita#IFRS17_APPA/IFRS17_P0526">group of contracts<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0159"/></ph></xref>.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>